101.description: In this session, we will take a look at how design shape modern application development
101.title: Why you should know about design

102.description: Why do we should make Progressive web app? How we can improve it? Google Workbox technology caching web app for ease of use.
102.title: Your next mobile app should be a Progressive Web App (PWA)

103.description: How to efficiently work with large amounts of data using the Paging Library
103.title: Android Architecture Library : Paging Library (Code Lab)

104.description: If you ask to a group of Android Developer how to execute a background task maybe they answer different api/techniques. It can be confusing but since last I/O, Google is providing a robust API to work in different scenarios and backwards compatibility. Come to this talk to learn more!
104.title: Deep Dive Work Manager

105.description: What's the difference between UI and UX ? Why UX is important ? How to become a UX Designer ?
105.title: UX is more than UI!

106.description: After 11 years of first iPhone released in 2007, mobile web is finally mature. Or does it? With all emerging and established techniques such as SPA, RWD, AMP, PWA, mobile web reach certain level but still have lot of problems. We gonna talk about them.
106.title: What is wrong with mobile web?

107.description: ဒီမှာက design (စနစ်တကျ စီစဉ် သတ်မှတ်ခြင်း) ဆိုတာကို decoration (ကြည့်ကောင်းအောင် ပြုလုပ်ခြင်း) နဲ့ တော်တော်များများ နားလည်မှု လွဲလေ့ ရှိပါတယ် ။  မတူညီတဲ့ design အမျိုးအစားတွေ ဖြစ်တဲ့ Idea Design, Workflow Design, Software Design, Feature Design စတာတွေရဲ့ အခြေခံ သဘောတရားတွေကို discuss ပြုလုပ်သွားပါမယ် ။
107.title: Mobile App တစ်ခု တည်ဆောက်မှု ပုံစံအား  Design အမြင်ဖြင့် ချဉ်းကပ်ခြင်း

108.description: Testing is a very important process of software development. Tests can define your product quality as well as make sure your code works as you intended to. The talk will cover how to start writing test on Android apps
108.title: Have You Met Test?

ye_linn_wai.bio: CEO and Co-Founder of Lae Lar Technology Co.,Ltd. , started his IT career since 15 years old and known as an author of best-seller Android books. He was also the Community Manager for the Google Developer Group Yangon & Technology Community Liaison at Phandeeyar and organized serval events; Google DevFest, Harvard CS50 Study Group & Android Study Jams in Yangon. Ye is passionate about transformative technology in education and founded edtech startup called LaeLar in 2017. He and his team of ed-tech enthusiasts are bringing the online learning platform for both Myanmar educators and learners.

peter_novak.bio: Peter is CTO at Kargo, a startup with the vision of transforming the logistics market in Myanmar by using technology to connect trucks, businesses and individuals. He graduated in Engineering Physics in Stockholm, and spent five years within software development at Ericsson before being selected for their international leadership program. This opportunity saw him being part of building the first telecom networks in Myanmar back in 2014. Peter now heads the team driving Kargo’s product design and development work
